_[test/toxcore/methods.c, line 21 [r2]](https://reviewable.io:443/reviews/toktok/hstox/14#-KMJNPBEx8mjAM5PerNf:-KMJNPBEx8mjAM5PerNg:595226324) ([raw file](https://github.com/toktok/hstox/blob/7f4537e26baff6c39de40298b9c5dcb4d3755751/test/toxcore/methods.c#L21)):_

> ``` C
>   CHECK (args.ptr[1].via.bin.size == crypto_box_NONCEBYTES);
> 
>   uint8_t combined_key[crypto_box_BEFORENMBYTES];
> ```

Instead of copying combined_key, nonce, and plain_text to temporary arrays, you can just pass them into encrypt_data_symmetric directly. You'll need to cast them, because they are `char*` instead of `uint8_t*`.

---

_[test/toxcore/methods.c, line 24 [r2]](https://reviewable.io:443/reviews/toktok/hstox/14#-KMJNiPIuI86nBRRaZvj:-KMJNiPJejA_gNkSsg_f:-769778346) ([raw file](https://github.com/toktok/hstox/blob/7f4537e26baff6c39de40298b9c5dcb4d3755751/test/toxcore/methods.c#L24)):_

> ``` C
>   uint8_t nonce[crypto_box_NONCEBYTES];
>   uint8_t plain_text[args.ptr[2].via.bin.size];
>   uint8_t cipher_text[sizeof (plain_text) + crypto_box_MACBYTES];
> ```

Style: write `sizeof plain_text` when plain_text is a variable. `sizeof (type)` is used for types.

---

_[test/toxcore/methods.c, line 32 [r2]](https://reviewable.io:443/reviews/toktok/hstox/14#-KMJNtGuAdBV9q7YeNq-:-KMJNtGuAdBV9q7YeNq0:-206593565) ([raw file](https://github.com/toktok/hstox/blob/7f4537e26baff6c39de40298b9c5dcb4d3755751/test/toxcore/methods.c#L32)):_

> ``` C
>   int len = encrypt_data_symmetric (combined_key, nonce, plain_text, sizeof plain_text, cipher_text);
>   if (len < 0)
>       return "An error occured while encryption process.";
> ```

Error messages like this (as opposed to log messages) should not be capitalised and should not have a "." at the end. The reason is that they should be written to be composable. Think of a chain of errors that can be connected using commas. For example, you write "an encryption error occurred" as your error message, and then a caller at a higher level can do: `"the test failed, because " + error`, and yet another higher level says `"won't deploy to production, because " + error`, and you end up with `"won't deploy to production, because the test failed, because an encryption error occurred"`.

> ```

Add return value check.
